description:
&lt;p&gt;Social Care Reablement (SCR) is a short term intervention service, supporting people to regain their independence through working towards personal goals in their own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a self-motivated occupational therapist with excellent goal setting and communication skills.   The role involves: the use of occupational therapy core skills; developing and presenting updated training to our team of support workers; managing a case load; screening complex referrals and providing peer support for team leaders through joint visits and peer supervisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, you will be part of a friendly, supportive team with regular supervision, appraisals, team meetings and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a Disclosure Barring Service disclosure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires the ability to fulfil all spoken aspects of the role with confidence and fluency in English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For additional information and/or informal discussion please contact Kay Bainbridge, Service Manager or Nadine Maddison Deputy Service Manager, on 01392 380593.&lt;/p&gt;
